problem: Completely simplify and rationalize the denominator: $$\frac{\sqrt{160}}{\sqrt{252}}\times\frac{\sqrt{245}}{\sqrt{108}}$$
solution: To begin, we can combine all of these square roots into a single square root: $$\frac{\sqrt{160}}{\sqrt{252}}\times\frac{\sqrt{245}}{\sqrt{108}}=\sqrt{\frac{160}{252}}\times\sqrt{\frac{245}{108}}=\sqrt{\frac{160\cdot245}{252\cdot108}}$$Now, simplify under the square root by canceling common factors.  To start, 160 and 108 are both divisible by 4.  252 and 160 also share a factor of 4.  This leaves us with: $$\sqrt{\frac{10\cdot245}{63\cdot27}}$$Looking carefully, we can see that 63 and 245 both share a factor of 7.  Cancel this, and simplify: $$\sqrt{\frac{10\cdot35}{9\cdot27}}=\frac{5}{9}\sqrt{\frac{14}{3}}=\boxed{\frac{5\sqrt{42}}{27}}$$
model_solution:
Step 1: Start by simplifying each square root in the expression: $$\frac{\sqrt{160}}{\sqrt{252}}\times\frac{\sqrt{245}}{\sqrt{108}}$$
$$\sqrt{160} = \sqrt{16\times10} = 4\sqrt{10}$$
$$\sqrt{252} = \sqrt{36\times7} = 6\sqrt{7}$$
$$\sqrt{245} = \sqrt{49\times5} = 7\sqrt{5}$$
$$\sqrt{108} = \sqrt{36\times3} = 6\sqrt{3}$$
$$\frac{\sqrt{160}}{\sqrt{252}}\times\frac{\sqrt{245}}{\sqrt{108}} = \frac{4\sqrt{10}}{6\sqrt{7}}\times\frac{7\sqrt{5}}{6\sqrt{3}}$$
Multiply the numerators and denominators: $$\frac{4\sqrt{10}}{6\sqrt{7}}\times\frac{7\sqrt{5}}{6\sqrt{3}} = \frac{4\cdot7\sqrt{10}\sqrt{5}}{6\cdot6\sqrt{7}\sqrt{3}} = \frac{28\sqrt{50}}{36\sqrt{21}}$$
Simplify the numerator: $$\frac{28\sqrt{50}}{36\sqrt{21}} = \frac{28\sqrt{2\cdot25}}{36\sqrt{7\cdot3}} = \frac{28\cdot5\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{21}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{21}}$$
$$\frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{21}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{3\cdot7}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{3}\sqrt{7}}$$
Multiply the numerator and denominator by $\sqrt{3}$ to rationalize the denominator: $\frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{3}\sqrt{7}} \times \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}} = \frac{140\sqrt{6}}{36\sqrt{21}}$
$$\frac{140\sqrt{6}}{36\sqrt{21}} = \frac{140\sqrt{6}}{36\sqrt{3}\sqrt{7}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}\sqrt{3}}{36\sqrt{3}\sqrt{7}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{7}} = \frac{140\sqrt{2}}{36\sqrt{7}}\times\frac{\sqrt{7}}{\sqrt{7}} = \frac{140\sqrt{14}}{36\cdot7}$$
$$\frac{140\sqrt{14}}{36\cdot7} = \frac{140\sqrt{14}}{252} = \frac{5\sqrt{14}}{9}$$
Multiply the numerator and denominator by $\sqrt{14}$ to rationalize the denominator: $\frac{5\sqrt{14}}{9} \times \frac{\sqrt{14}}{\sqrt{14}} = \frac{5\sqrt{196}}{9\sqrt{14}}$
$\frac{5\sqrt{196}}{9\sqrt{14}} = \frac{5\sqrt{4\cdot49}}{9\sqrt{14}} = \frac{5\cdot7\sqrt{4}}{9\sqrt{14}} = \frac{35\cdot2}{9\sqrt{14}} = \frac{70}{9\sqrt{14}}$

Note: This is not the final answer.
